a brilliant book ! finally ! a book detailing the most imaginative and thought provoking type of film available : the indie . american independant cinema has consistently produced fresh , off center films , especially from the likes of richard linklater , kevin smith and hal hartley . they 're all in here , as well as discussions on films such as the seminal slackers . to sum up , if you 're interested in more than just special effects laden pulp when it comes to movies , buy this book